<:p>- The plays that William Shakespeare saw in Coventry during his boyhood or 'teens' may have influenced how his plays, such as "Hamlet", came about.</:p>
<:p>- Cyprus and Venice are the two main settings for "Othello". Cyprus was formally annexed by Venice in 1489, and remained part of the Venetian Empire until 1570. The play was written in 1603.</:p>
