<:p>- Illyria is a region in western Balkan Peninsula where Shakespeare's most famous fictional comedy, Twelfth Night takes place. It is also mentioned in the Part 2 of "Henry VI": "Being captain of a pinnace, threatens more // Than Bargulus the strong Illyrian pirate."</:p>
<:p>- Inverness in "Macbeth"</:p>
<:p>- Jerusalem Chamber appeared in scene IV of Shakespare's "Henry IV, Part 2". The king is taken there to die to compensate for the fact he never made his promised crusade to Jerusalem itself.</:p>
<:p>- Shakespeare used the tale of Henry V receiving the insulting gift of tennis balls from the French Dauphin at Kenilworth for dramatic effect in "Henry V", Act 1, scene 2.</:p>
